			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Gamepads, <a name="22605"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 19 04 7:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>On my first bard (rolled Dec 1999), I bought a gamepad extremely early on due to all the problems I was having with wrist fatigue. I don't remember what the name of that gamepad was, it had six buttons and a rudder wheel that I was able to map for Alt-Left and Alt-Right. Using this, I could strafe and twist with my left hand while doing normal turns and forward/backward movement with my right hand. This was a lot more urgent of a need on a PvP server because of jousting.
<br />

<br />
I retired that bard shortly after --edit: Kunark, not Velious-- was released, and the gamepad went in the closet.
<br />

<br />
I moved to a blue server recently and started a new bard. Maybe it's just me, but it feels like songs take 1 second longer to &quot;cast&quot; now than they did then. Whether true or not, the strain of twisting doesn't effect me like it did back then, so I haven't been using my gamepad.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
