				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Gamepads, <a name="22689"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 20 04 10:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I use the Nostromo N52, though I find I don't actually macro twists with it much.  I thought it would work nicely for the Marr-Muse-Zek routine, but I just don't wind up doing that with it much.
<br />

<br />
What it is very nice for is setting up the /stopsong, cast sequence without committing hotbuttons to each song.  So I can twist with one button press per song instead of two.
<br />

<br />
Also nice having movement and a few other keys all accessible to one hand.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
