				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Gamepads, <a name="22697"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 20 04 11:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Gamepads tend to be better ergonomically designed for repetitive button pushing than a keyboard (the standard Qwerty keyboard layout was designed to slow down typing to avoid jamming typewriters).  This by itself can be good enough to avoid any carpal tunnel problems you might get from the keyboard.  Personally I avoid macros, I just have my gamepad (Gravis gamepad pro) set up to emulate me hitting a different number key for each button.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
