				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm using the Nostromo N52.  I have had it for a couple of weeks now and am still trying to come up with the best config for my toon.  Hard part about using the N52 is the fact you can do almost everything on it and that just creates to many choices for me so I can't decide on what I like and don't like.
<br />

<br />
So far i've just remapped all of my &quot;critical&quot; keys onto the N52, including movement onto the gamepad thumb buttons.  I've found that my game play hasn't changed much, but my wrist hasn't suffered from any soreness or fatigue after I started using the N52 gamepad.
<br />

<br />
Overall, I think the gamepad hasn't necessarily increased my ability to twist and/or help me become a better bard (at least not yet), but it has improved my comfort level when playing.
<br />

<br />
Moezart
<br />
14th Half Elf Bard
<br />
Veeshan</span></td>
