				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a strategic commander, can do every function I want it to including auto-twist 4 songs while accounting for missed notes etc. Just a pain in the arse to get it all set up but when its done, its dreamy ;)
<br />

<br />
Sigh, I lost the profile from my last reformat <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" />and havent hooked it back up yet, since ive mostly been soloing and like to use my hands for that. God only knows ill hook it back up when it comes time for grouping ;)
<br />

<br />
Heres a picture of it: <img src="http://www.gamersdepot.com/accessories/microsoft/strategic_commander/product_shot2.jpg">
<br />

<br />
Each button can be macroed, and you can switch between 3 sets of the 6 buttons by using the 3 on the side.
<br />

<br />
That is per profile, and you can switch between 3 on the fly, so its pretty much limitless.
<br />

<br />
The top also moves in any fashion on the base should you want to use that feature and there is a scroll button on the right to zoom in and out.
<br />

<br />
Very helpful when setup right imo!</span></td>
