				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Gamepads, <a name="33186"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 6 04 12:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I recently got the Nostromo 52 but I'm still pretty set in my ways, and haven't really used it much. I'm taking baby steps, as it were. I did map most of my normal hotkeys in it, and even put a twist of songs 3-6. I do find that it's not as reliable to twist 4 songs, and it's not just missed notes. Lacking patience, I haven't really sat and fiddled to figure out exactly what is happening. I mapped the movement in soe of the keyboard keys, and figured I'd start small and use it for movement and sometimes my asisst and autoattack, always my stopsong. 
<br />

<br />
I may end up moving around my mapping and just having my song macros in there instead, since it's so much more comfortable on the wrist. I also mapped my /stopsong hotkey to F11, so that I could program the Nostromo to run macros using that and not fudge up if I'm typing already. 
<br />

<br />
I have to say, it's pretty great. I just ordered another one for my bot computer, since I have a thought that it'll be great for actual timed complete heal chains. Hoping the delay in the Nostromo will not cause problems like /pause in EQ does. With a bot cleric, if I'm not focusing on her 100%, I prefer to not have to count out the CH chain as well as concentrate on either bard or chanter as well.</span></td>
