				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Gamepads, <a name="33213"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 6 04 3:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I bought one recently, and had plans to set it up to run circles for me to do AE kiting.  But it turns out that it doesn't help that much for that.   But it is pretty good for chant kiting.  I have a pretty elaborate twist programmed in that throws in angstlich's assonance every 3rd round of four songs.  It probably lowers my DPS slightly because of missed notes and &quot;your songs ends.&quot; messages due to terrain, but overall it's a slight win just because I can concentrate better on my kiting path, and if we root the mob, it's a cake walk.
<br />

<br />
The best use I've found for it, though, is tradeskills.  With the new tradeskill interface, I can just load up a bunch of materials in my bags, select a recipe, place my cursor on the Combine button and have the macro left click, delay then click my /autoinv hot key, and repeat that about every 2 seconds.   It's REALLY nice.  Shh... don't tell the people at eqtraders... they'll have a cow.... &quot;I clicked my fingers to the bone, got incurable carpal tunnel so that I could GM in every tradeskill!... now they nerf my accomplishments by making a new interface that anyone can use, and is easier to macro&quot;.</span></td>
